{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"def29cc7-a33b-43fb-97a5-45eb18655524","content":"Here's the mapping from VSTest → Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n| VSTest flag | MTP equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/[Category=Integration]/\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5min` |\n\n**New command** (running the test executable directly, which is the MTP model):\n\n```bash\ndotnet exec <TestApp>.dll \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/[Category=Integration]/\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5min\n```\n\nOr via `dotnet test` with `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in your project:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/[Category=Integration]/\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5min\n```\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**Key gotcha:** MTP uses tree-node filter syntax (`/[Property=Value]/`), not the VSTest `--filter` expression syntax. Double-check your trait names match what your test framework reports.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e1721076-63b0-46da-aad6-6c1358789c24","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a codebase task. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nLet me think about the mappings:\n\n1. `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` → In MTP, filtering uses `--filter` but the syntax might differ. Actually, MTP uses `--filter` as well but the trait-based filtering syntax is slightly different. With MSTest on MTP, `Category=Integration` maps to `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` or using the `--treenode-filter` syntax.\n\n\n2. `--logger trx` → MTP uses `--report-trx` (if using the TRX report extension)\n3. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → MTP uses `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, and format can be specified with `--coverage-output-format cobertura`\n4. `--blame-crash` → MTP uses `--crashdump` (via crash dump extension)\n5. `--blame-hang` → MTP uses `--hangdump`\n6. `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → MTP uses `--hangdump-timeout` with the timeout value\n\nI need to clarify how MTP integrates with `dotnet test`. When using `dotnet test` with MTP enabled via the project file setting, options after `--` get forwarded to MTP. With .NET 9+, there's native MTP support in `dotnet test`, but on .NET 8 you'd run the test executable directly or use a compatibility layer. Let me think through the exact command syntax for different .NET versions. I need to clarify the exact package dependencies and command syntax for MTP with .NET 8. The key packages are `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` along with the extension packages for reporting, coverage, and diagnostics, and when running through `dotnet run`, I pass the arguments after `--` to reach the test executable directly.\n\nNow I'm mapping the VSTest flag equivalents to their MTP counterparts—things like `--filter` for test selection, `--report-trx` for test result reporting, and the crash/hang dump options for diagnostics. Some of these mappings need verification since the MTP API is still evolving.","outputTokens":1691},"id":"8b910af7-94b9-4fb4-9097-1e59fb660ada","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:06:21.983Z","parentId":"8befde1e-8975-4bd6-8fed-a54fb4edac72"}
